6. virgines leem etc. There were 27 girls and 27 boys. This number (ter noveni) appears to have been usual in Roman choruses: Livy xxvu. 37 and xxxx. 12.

bem—custos. Each epithet belongs to both boys and girls (cf. 111. 4. 18, 19). They were to be children of parents religiously married (confarreati), of patrician or at least senatorial rank, and patrimi et matrimi (i. e. having both parents living, ἀμφιθαλεῖς).
